  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Landscape and Workplace Safety Coordinator",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Description</strong></u></p><ul><li>Oversee and supervise all landscaping works within the works area</li><li>Able to work offshore, in oil and gas industry environment</li><li>Liase with officers/management agents with regards to work arrangements, site inspections, meetings, feedback, complaints or any other matters</li><li>Prepare routine work schedules and service reports as well as attend to ad-hoc job request</li><li>Prepare safety documents like permit-to-work, risk assessment and method of statement.</li><li>Brief and execute work according to safety procedures, protocol and guidelines</li><li>Provide horticultural advice on plant maintenance, selection and planting works</li><li>Work in a diverse working environment</li><li>Handle adhoc work request beyond normal working hours if necessary</li></ul><p><u><strong>Job Requirements</strong></u></p><ul><li>Minimum 3 years experience in oil and gas industry / work environment</li><li>Minimum Diploma in Horticulture and Landscape / WSQ Advanced Certificate in Landscape Supervision or other equivalent qualifications</li><li>Holds relevant workplace safety certifications, including managing work at height</li><li>Possess a minimum class 3 license (Preferably)</li><li>Good command of written and spoken English</li><li>Good knowledge in plant ID</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft office, Photoshop</li><li>Team player, proactive and independent</li></ul>",
